<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="518" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1014,2013]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1086,1112]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Description</emphasis>
. Male. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[427,491,1087,1113]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Head</emphasis>
. Face and antenna concolorous brown, maxillary palpus pale brown. Eye bridge 2 facets wide. Face with about 20 setae. Clypeus with 2 setae. Maxillary palpus with 2 segments (2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1229,1245,1122,1136]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">nd</superScript>
and 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1312,1326,1122,1136]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">rd</superScript>
segments partly fused); 1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[321,332,1159,1173]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">st</superScript>
segment with 4 setae, with large dorsal pit with sensilla; surface of antennal flagellomeres smooth, body of 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[260,273,1194,1208]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">th</superScript>
antennal flagellomere 2.3x as long as wide, neck shorter than wide, longest setae longer than width of flagellomere. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[308,404,1231,1257]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Thorax.</emphasis>
Brown; setae pale. Anterior pronotum with 4 setae. Proepisternum with 7 setae. Scutellum with 2 long and some short and fine setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[637,702,1266,1292]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Wing</emphasis>
(in poor condition in the specimen studied). Hyaline. Length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
. Width/length and anal lobe not detectable in the specimen studied. Veins distinct, except for stM. c/w 0.65. Halter yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[313,369,1339,1365]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Legs</emphasis>
. Brown; setae pale. Fore tibial organ forming large patch of setae in demarcated depression. Fore tibial spur shorter than apical width of tibia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[645,762,1374,1400]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Pale brown; setae pale and moderately sized. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1281,1437,1374,1400]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[160,247,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1944,1968]" captionTargetBox="[297,1288,206,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-17@15.[277,1311,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 8. Hypopygium, ventral. A. Lycoriella nivicola sp. n. (paratype from Greenland). B. L. pearyi sp. n. (holotype). Scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5751569" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5751569/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). Pale brown, like abdomen. Intergonocoxal area moderately long, with wide setose lobe. Gonocoxa wide, longer than gonostylus, with sparse setosity, shortest in apical fourth. Gonostylus (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1143,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[176,1423,195,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-20@16.[161,1427,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Gonostylus, ventral. A. Lycoriella longa sp. n. (paratype). B. L. nivicola sp. n. (holotype). C. L. parva (Holmgren, 1869) (from Canada, Kuujjuarapik). D. L. pearyi sp. n. (holotype). Scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5751571" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5751571/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
) long and narrow, apically narrowed, weakly impressed; with short setosity, densely setose apically, with strong apical tooth, 9–10 megasetae medially, megasetae straight, shorter than apical tooth; with well-differentiated whip-lash seta on basal third of gonostylus. Tegmen longer than wide, roundish apically, straight laterally, weakly sclerotized, with small area of tiny aedeagal teeth. Aedeagal apodeme long and strong.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1014,2013]" box="[199,381,1627,1653]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,249,1627,1653]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">BIN</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="519" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,1014,2013]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="519" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1662,1688]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Discussion</emphasis>
. In having the maxillary palpus 2-segmented, 
<taxonomicName authority="Menzel &amp; Vilkamaa, 2021" authorityName="Menzel &amp; Vilkamaa" authorityYear="2021" box="[850,1044,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pearyi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[850,1044,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Lycoriella pearyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1051,1115,1663,1689]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1051,1115,1663,1689]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schmitz, 1919)" baseAuthorityName="Schmitz" baseAuthorityYear="1919" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felix">
<emphasis box="[1242,1320,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">L. felix</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schmitz, H." pageId="17" pageNumber="518" pagination="25 - 32" refId="ref18699" refString="Schmitz, H. (1919) V. - Zur Kenntnis der Gattung Bradysia Winnertz (Sciaridae, Dipt.). Zoologische Mededeelingen, 5, 25 - 32." type="journal article" year="1919">Schmitz, 1919</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry box="[406,587,1699,1725]" name="Netherlands" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">the Netherlands</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Mohrig &amp; Mamaev, 1983" authorityName="Mohrig &amp; Mamaev" authorityYear="1983" box="[600,1061,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis box="[600,756,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">L. deserticola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mohrig, W. &amp; Mamaev, B. &amp; Krivosheina, N." box="[765,1061,1699,1725]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" pagination="141 - 155" refId="ref17941" refString="Mohrig, W., Mamaev, B. &amp; Krivosheina, N. (1983) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Trauermucken der Sowjetunion (Diptera, Sciaridae). Teil V. Sciariden aus Mittelasien. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Okologie und Geographie der Tiere, 110 (2), 141 - 155." type="journal article" year="1983">Mohrig &amp; Mamaev, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1254,1383,1699,1725]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mohrig &amp; Mamaev, 1985" authorityName="Mohrig &amp; Mamaev" authorityYear="1985" box="[151,552,1734,1761]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stylata">
<emphasis box="[151,256,1735,1761]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">L. stylata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mohrig, W. &amp; Krivosheina, N. &amp; Mamaev, B." box="[263,552,1734,1761]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" pagination="299 - 310" refId="ref18000" refString="Mohrig, W., Krivosheina, N. &amp; Mamaev, B. (1985) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Trauermucken (Diptera, Sciaridae) der Sowjetunion. Teil VIII: Neue Arten aus europaischen Gebieten. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Okologie und Geographie der Tiere, 112 (3), 299 - 310." type="journal article" year="1985">Mohrig &amp; Mamaev, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, described from the European part of 
<collectingCountry box="[976,1053,1735,1761]" name="Russia" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Russia</collectingCountry>
, all of which may have the palpus either three- or two-segmented. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Menzel &amp; Vilkamaa" authorityYear="2021" box="[508,701,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pearyi">
<emphasis box="[508,701,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Lycoriella pearyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<emphasis box="[846,931,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmitz" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[846,926,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felix">L. felix</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mohrig &amp; Mamaev" authorityYear="1983" box="[1125,1278,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserticola">
<emphasis box="[1125,1278,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">L. deserticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mohrig &amp; Mamaev" authorityYear="1985" box="[1332,1437,1771,1797]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stylata">
<emphasis box="[1332,1437,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">L. stylata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a distinct intergonocoxal lobe and five megasetae on the apical half of its gonostylus, whereas the other species have at most a row of setae on the intergonocoxal area and two or three subapical gonostylar megasetae. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Menzel &amp; Vilkamaa" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,343,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pearyi">
<emphasis box="[151,343,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Lycoriella pearyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmitz" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[486,562,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felix">
<emphasis box="[486,562,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">L. felix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the eye bridge continuous, with two to three rows of facets, a normal, not a very narrow wing, and an undivided intergonocoxal lobe, whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmitz" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[957,1034,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="felix">
<emphasis box="[957,1034,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">L. felix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the eye bridge broken medially, with a discontinuous single row of facets, a strongly reduced wing and distinctly two intergonocoxal lobes. The hypopygium of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Menzel &amp; Vilkamaa" authorityYear="2021" box="[329,522,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pearyi">
<emphasis box="[329,522,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">Lycoriella pearyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Menzel &amp; Vilkamaa, 2021" authorityName="Menzel &amp; Vilkamaa" authorityYear="2021" box="[800,919,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nivicola" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[800,919,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">L. nivicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[925,988,1987,2013]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[925,988,1987,2013]" pageId="17" pageNumber="518" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
but the latter can be distinguished by its two-segmented palpus, narrower gonostylus which is more evenly narrowed towards apex, in having the gonostylar megasetae relatively longer, and in being smaller (wing length 1.9 
<emphasis box="[898,970,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">versus</emphasis>
<quantity box="[977,1116,186,213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="18" pageNumber="519" unit="mm" value="2.3" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.1">2.1–2.5 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="519" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,223,249]" pageId="18" pageNumber="519">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species is named after the polar explorer Robert Edwin Peary (1856–1920), one of the pioneers in the study of 
